* I will think for a bit about adding more explanation on moving around the J. The fact that you only say PUT J 16 (and not 'as which stone') in fact implies that J can either be 4Y or 9Y - only for display matters there must be a consistent rule (like 'display to the right'). And the idea that you would want a TAKE and PUT to shuffle J inside a row would imply something like TAKE J 16 -> PUT J 16, which is weird. But maybe I can add to 'display to the right' that this does not mean that J has taken that value, or that J can take any value within a row (but that is already the nature of J).

* Explanation of TAKE and PUT: I did add in "One action can be either to take a tile from a row, to put a tile in a row, or to combine two rows", before listing the format of those actions. Maybe I am too deep into this puzzle to realize what is not yet clear: how can I explain more about what TAKE and PUT do?

* Outstanding issues that I will make you aware of when solved/changed: 
- J vs leftmost / 14 value;
- Possibly including cases that strictly test the max 4 per set / 13 per run versus J;
- Cleaning the cases for more than two identical tiles;
- Reorder input of some cases.
